article.description: Conner Toolson had 22 points as Utah Valley won its seventh consecutive game, topping Cal State Bakersfield 76-61 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Toolson carries Utah Valley past CS Bakersfield 76-61
article.linkText: Toolson carries Utah Valley past CS Bakersfield 76-61
article.story: OREM, Utah -- Conner Toolson had 22 points as Utah Valley won its seventh consecutive game, topping Cal State Bakersfield 76-61 on Saturday night. Jake Toolson had 13 points and seven rebounds for Utah Valley (23-8, 12-4 Western Athletic Conference). Ben Nakwaasah added 11 points. Richard Harward had 11 rebounds and three blocks for the hosts. Rickey Holden had 15 points for the Roadrunners (16-14, 7-9) whose losing streak reached five games. Jarkel Joiner, the Roadrunners' leading scorer heading into the contest at 16 points per game, scored 7 points on 3-of-13 shooting. The Wolverines evened the season series against the Roadrunners with the win. Cal State Bakersfield defeated Utah Valley 73-71 on Jan. 5. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
